sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I52001
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: ccdB and nonfunctional pUC19 derived high copy origin
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is designed to be located in the multiple cloning site of low copy BioBrick vectors. BBa_P1016 provides selection against non-insert containing clones and BBa_I50020 enables the base vector to be propagated at high copy for ease of purification
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This part is a composite part of BBa_P1016 and BBa_I50020. It is designed to be placed in the multiple cloning site of BioBricks vectors. Vectors with this part in the multiple cloning site will be selected against during BioBricks assembly because BBa_P1016 is lethal to most cell strains. Also, BBa_I50020 enables the vector to be propagated at high copy regardless of the other origins on the vector.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: ccdB
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is a differs from BBa_P1011 in that the mutations introduced in BBa_P1011 to remove restriction sites are not present in this part. It does have the "normal" ccd promoter and ccdB coding region. It also has a double TAA stop codon as per BioBrick conventions.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This part is derived from BBa_P1010 but it lacks ccdA-.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: ccdA- was eliminated since it is an inactive form of ccdA and should not be required for the toxic phenotype of ccdB.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: pUC19 ori
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Minimal pUC19-derived high copy replication origin
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: High copy origin of replication derived from pSB1A3. Designed to omit antibiotic resistance markers and primer binding sites.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
